description:
daemon/src/jmap.rs message_query() (line 2514): the limit parameter from the JMAP request is validated only to be non-negative, then passed directly as the SQL LIMIT argument to store.query_messages():

    let limit = args.get("limit").and_then(|v| v.as_i64()).unwrap_or(256);
    if limit < 0 { return invalid_args(...); }
    let ids = store.query_messages(&chat_id, position, limit).await?;

And query_messages() in daemon/src/store.rs:1766:
    SELECT id FROM message WHERE chat_id = ? AND deleted_at IS NULL
    ORDER BY received_at ASC LIMIT ? OFFSET ?

A request with limit=9223372036854775807 (i64::MAX) causes SQLite to attempt returning every row in the table, with results allocated into a Vec<String>. All other query methods in the store have hardcoded LIMIT 1000 or 10000 caps.

Consistent with nie-u966.8 (Space/query no pagination). Fix: cap at a maximum (e.g. 4096) and return hasMore: true if clamped.
